	<tag>
		<description>
			<![CDATA[
    
The ECruiser Calendar is an easy-to-use, AJAX-enabled component.
 It consists of two primary components: Calendar and DateInput.  You can use the static calendar component where users select the date directly, or you can provide an input with a popup calendar.
 Among other customizable features, Calendar allows you to: show both today and selected date with separate styles and
 to include icons in the Calendar navigator.
 Calendar allows you to modify properties that define the year range to display within the Calendar. By defining the minYear and maxYear properties, you specify the earliest and latest years that the related Calendar drop down list will display.
        
  ]]>
		</description>
		<name>calendar</name>
		<tag-class>ecruiser.tag.CalendarTag</tag-class>
		<body-content>JSP</body-content>
