	<tag>
		<description>
			<![CDATA[
    
 TabControl is the primary ECruiser TabControl interface.
 It is the physical collection of tabs, and the container that defines the overall TabControl properties.
 TabControl includes a variety of properties that allow you to customize its appearance and
 define its functionality.
 You can create TabControls in one of four orientations: horizontal, vertical, left, or right.
 You can define whether tabs are allowed to wrap if the control exceeds the alotted space.
 You can also define whether tab text is allowed to wrap to the next line if the text exceeds the alotted tab space.
 TabControl supports assigning image backgrounds to tabs, which allows you to create elegant, modern-looking tabs.
 Tabs can also stretch automatically to accommodate text of varying lengths.
 TabControl allows you to use facets to customize tabs, which includes adding standard JSF components as needed.
 TabControl implementations can be constructed by:
 Defining Tabs in the JSP with Tags.
 Defining a TabControl with JSF SelectItem Objects.
 Manipulating Tabs Programmatically.
 TabControl supports event handling and provides three ways to notify applications of occurring events:
 1.	Assigning one or more selection listeners to the menu itself.
 2.	Using the standard JSF action and actionListener properties on individual menu cells.
 3.	Using any of the generic JavaScript event attributes on the TabControl or Tabs.
 Like most JSF components, TabControl supports all standard JavaScript event attributes in the client,
 but ECruiser adds a powerful, JSF server-side event mechanism as well.
 TabControl supports dragging and dropping TabControl cells to reorder Tabs within a TabControl.
    
  ]]>
		</description>
		<name>tabcontrol</name>
		<tag-class>ecruiser.advanced.tab.tag.TabControlTag</tag-class>
		<body-content>JSP</body-content>
