	<tag>
		<description>
			<![CDATA[
    
    A Tab is an individual item within the tab control. A TabControl can contain one or more Tabs.
TabControl includes various properties to help you create the look and feel you want for your Tabs.
You can aslo define custom styles for individual Tabs.
You can assign your own custom icon images to Tabs to enhance the usability of your TabControl.
A Tab can appear in one of four states: normal, hover, disabled, or selected.
The Tab's appearance and behavior are determined by its state.
You can define whether Tabs are allowed to wrap if the control exceeds the alotted space.
You can also define whether Tab text is allowed to wrap to the next line if the text exceeds the alotted Tab space.
TabControl supports assigning image backgrounds to tabs, which allows you to create elegant, modern-looking tabs.
Tabs can also stretch automatically to accommodate text of varying lengths.
TabControl allows you to use facets to customize tabs, which includes adding standard JSF components as needed.
    
  ]]>
		</description>
		<name>tab</name>
		<tag-class>ecruiser.advanced.tab.tag.TabTag</tag-class>
