		</attribute>
		<attribute>
			<description>
				<![CDATA[
        
         The style class applied on the menu cells. A menu cell is the cell which is not placed   <br>
         on the menu bar. Style class applied on a menu cell can be specified also as a   <br>
         comma separated value list of style classes. A menu cell is divided into four areas <br>
         as follows : <br>
         <p>
            <ul>
                <li>left area : for icon if specified or any other custom component</li>
                <li>text area : for menu cell text</li>
                <li>shortCut area : for shortcut key text</li>
                <li>right area : for expand icon if menu cell has children or for any custom component.</li>
            </ul>
         </p><br>
         Comma separated value list contains 5 style classes. The order is the <br>
         following : overall menu cell style class, left style class, text style class, shourcut key <br>
         style class and right style class. Any of the style class values from comma separated list can be empty <br>

         The default is <code>menuCell</code>
      
      ]]>
			</description>
