	</tag>

	<tag>
		<description>
			<![CDATA[
      The primary table component for dynamically rendering text data, links and/or field component into a grid-style
      table. The overall layout is a series of rows with a single cell.
      Datatable has a fully costomizable look and feel by using cascading style sheets. There are defined properties
      for setting style for all major parts. For datarow can be defined alternating styles for example for odd and even
      rows.
      Are defined also sorting and column behaviors.
    ]]>
		</description>
		<name>datatable</name>
		<tag-class>ecruiser.advanced.datatable.tag.DataTableTag</tag-class>
		<body-content>JSP</body-content>
		<attribute>
			<description>
				<![CDATA[
        The flag that controls whether events of this component use the AJAX request mechanism or not.
      ]]>
			</description>
			<name>ajax</name>
			<required>false</required>
			<deferred-value>
				<type>
					boolean
				</type>
			</deferred-value>
		</attribute>
		<attribute>
			<description>
				<![CDATA[
           
        The flag indicating whether DataTable should load rows using AJAX requests.
        This way DataTable will render a minimum number of rows and load through AJAX requests other rows
        if it is scrolled into an area with no rows.
        This will allow you to display millions of records with good and constant performance.
        Performance may vary depending on the renderer or browser.
        
        ]]>
			</description>
			<name>ajaxLoading</name>
			<required>false</required>
			<deferred-value>
				<type>
					boolean
				</type>
			</deferred-value>
		</attribute>
		<attribute>
			<description>
